Description: Concave lip sherd (rim missing) of Attic black-glazed pottery open vessel, probably cup; wholly glazed with remains of added white diagonal lines; inscription cut on exterior.
Curator's comments: The added colour and the form of phi suggest a date into the fourth century, though not the alpha.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.2017)
